[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] The numbers $\sigma _{\ell j}^{2}$ and $\mu _{\ell }$ can be shown to be the covariances and means of the variables in the process.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] For general stochastic processes strict-sense stationarity implies wide-sense stationarity but not every wide-sense stationary stochastic process is strict-sense stationary.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] However, for a Gaussian stochastic process the two concepts are equivalent.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] Therefore, stationary Gaussian process is completely determined by its one-parameter mean function and covariance function.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] There is an explicit representation for stationary Gaussian processes.
