[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] The parameter $\ell$ is the characteristic length-scale of the process (practically, "how close" two points x and $x'$ have to be to influence each other significantly), *$\delta$* is the Kronecker delta and $\sigma$ the standard deviation of the noise fluctuations.
