[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] A Wiener process (also known as Brownian motion) is the integral of a white noise generalized Gaussian process.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] It is not stationary, but it has stationary increments.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] The Ornstein–Uhlenbeck process is a stationary Gaussian process.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] The Brownian bridge is (like the Ornstein–Uhlenbeck process) an example of a Gaussian process whose increments are not independent.
[src:hyperparameter-tuning/gaussian-process] The fractional Brownian motion is a Gaussian process whose covariance function is a generalisation of that of the Wiener process.
